replies.body:
Well with that in mind, I should probably list the usual full build for me:

{{item:3047}} {{item:1401}} {{item:3071}} {{item:3748}} {{item:3742}} {{item:3102}} 

And then I'd cap out cdr somehow with scaling cdr runes. This season though, you need more of that without the low-level cdr mastery. There also was always a toss-up between using lifesteal quints for super-sustain early and sacrificing mr glyphs for more scaling cdr quints, or keep traditional glyphs and sacrificising early sustain for scaling cdr quints instead. Really don't know how I'd approach this route in full these days with the new masteries, jungle items, and pots. Haven't spent enough time trying out different things.

I'm guessing Vi tests are next on my teambuilder spam list. {{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}} 


P.S. I resent the lack of one-Vimoticon-per-post in this thread's responses. {{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

Nice, nice. Yeah that's a strong one. Not all that much attack speed but lots of tank and a good amount of AD and armor shredding. Runes are kinda questionable IMO but hey if it worked for you, then it worked.
Here are my tanky AD builds without a jungle item:

{{item:3153}} {{item:3111}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3742}} {{item:3748}} {{item:3065}} 
Or:
{{item:3153}} {{item:3111}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3742}} {{item:3074}} {{item:3078}} 

Those were some of my more fun builds, and you can see I stuck to a few certain items.
Again, opinion is strong with this champion. There are so many ways to play her, and most of them are effective and a lot of the time it depends on the type of team you're playing against.
Happy punching!
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}

P.S. on another note, tiamat early was much stronger on Vi in S5. I'd used to go cinder into tiamat, and farm like crazy while providing a lot of dps in ganks. Of course, it no longer works that way, so my build route may actually prove to be weak at many points in the game in S6. I don't know, but we'll find out. Discovery requires experimentation! ... ... buuuut not the creepy Marvel-hydra evil-mastermind/human-rights-violation kind.

EDIT: woops! almost forgot... {{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}} 

I'm sorry, but vimoticons are just eye-candy. {{sticker:slayer-pantheon-popcorn}} 
Literally! They're pink!

Yeah that's powerful. But like you said, you're full AD relying on flat AD and not much attack speed to get you through much with sustained damage. The passive on her W is powerful, I'll admit, but the AD scaling is better on her ulti, so using full AD like that is just another way to play her. Like I said earlier in another comment, Vi can be played a number of ways, and hardly any of them are wrong, they're based on what they think works best and what they can rely on. There's no wrong way to play her, really.

Thanks for your opinion!
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
